{"article_id":"dvrr9ToAPbM5nLuS","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"US President Donald Trump has said","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"he could declare a national emergency","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"to build a US-Mexico border wall","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"without the approval of Congress .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"It came","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"after he met senior Democrats ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"who refused his requests for funding .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"The stand-off has seen Mr Trump withhold support for a bill","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"to fully fund the government","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"until he gets money for the border wall .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"He said","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"he was prepared for the partial government shutdown","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"- now in its third week -","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"to last years .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Around 800,000 federal workers have been without pay since 22 December .","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"Trump aides and lawmakers will meet later on Saturday in a fresh bid","depth":3},{"id":16,"text":"to resolve the impasse .","depth":3},{"id":17,"text":"The Republican president initially gave a positive account of the 90-minute meeting at the White House ,","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"describing it as `` very productive '' .","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"But","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"when asked","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"whether he had considered using emergency presidential powers","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"to bypass congressional approval of funding ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Mr Trump said","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"he had .","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"`` I may do it .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"We can call a national emergency","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"and build it very quickly .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"That 's another way","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"of doing it . ''","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"`` I 'm very proud of doing what I 'm doing , ''","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"the president added .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"`` I do n't call it a shutdown ,","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"I call it doing what you have to do for the benefit and safety of our country . ''","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"Friday 's meeting had been `` contentious '' ,","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"while Senate Democratic leader Chuck Schumer said :","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"`` We told the president","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"we needed the government open .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"He resisted . ''","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"Donald Trump says","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"he can declare a `` national emergency ''","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"and build his promised wall along the border","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"without congressional approval .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"If that 's the case ,","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"the question becomes why he does n't go ahead and do that .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Why put federal workers through the pain","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"of forgoing pay","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"and hamstring key government agencies ,","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"including the Department of Homeland Security ,","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"if he could bypass Democratic objections with the snap of his presidential fingers ?","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"The answer is because the solution is n't that simple .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"There are provisions of US law","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"that allow the president to direct military construction projects during war or national emergency ,","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"but that money would have to come from Defence Department funds","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"allocated by Congress for other purposes .","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"Such a move may prompt Congress ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"including Republicans ,","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"to push back .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"Then there 's the inevitable legal challenge from Democrats to such an exercise of presidential authority .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Any presidential order","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"to build a wall","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"would be met by an equally imposing wall of court filings","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"blocking its construction .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"The president 's latest suggestions are best viewed as simply another attempt","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"to gain the upper hand in negotiations with Democrats .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"Democrats ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"who now hold the majority in the House ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"passed spending bills on Thursday","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"to reopen the government ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"including $ 1.3bn","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"( £1bn )","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"of border security funds until 8 February .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"But the legislation can not take effect","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"unless it passes the Republican-controlled Senate ,","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"where leader Mitch McConnell said","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"his party would not back any measure","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"without the president 's support .","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"The Kentucky senator called the Democratic budget `` a time-wasting act of political posturing '' .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"In Friday 's news conference , Mr Trump also told reporters","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"he might consider asking his cabinet to decline a $ 10,000 raise","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"that is due to take effect","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"because a pay freeze has expired as an inadvertent result of the shutdown .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"The fiscal fiasco began","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"when Congress and Mr Trump failed to reach an agreement over a budget bill in December .","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"The Republicans had passed an initial funding bill","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"including $ 5bn","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"( £4bn )","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"for the wall ,","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"when they still had a majority in the House ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"but they could not get the necessary 60 votes in the 100-seat Senate .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"Two vulnerable Republican senators","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"up for re-election in 2020","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"- Cory Gardner of Colorado and Susan Collins of Maine -","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"have broken ranks","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"to back approving the budget","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"and ending the shutdown .","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"The White House is again floating the idea of a deal for `` Dreamers '' -","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"immigrants","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"who illegally entered the US as children .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"Democrats want to ensure","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"that these individuals are shielded from deportation ,","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"but have insisted","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"that they will not support a deal over wall funding .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"Vice-President Mike Pence told Fox News","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"the deal was being `` talked about '' ,","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"but that Mr Trump said","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"no deal was possible `` without a wall '' .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"About 25 % of the US federal government has no funding","depth":5},{"id":109,"text":"Nine departments have been affected ,","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"including Homeland Security , Justice , Housing , Agriculture , Commerce , Interior , and the Treasury","depth":6},{"id":111,"text":"Native American tribes","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"who receive substantial federal funding","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"are struggling","depth":6},{"id":114,"text":"More women than ever before won seats in Congress in the 2018 mid-terms .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":229,"left":131,"right":228,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":129,"right":130,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":121,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":118,"right":120,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":0,"right":117,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":117,"left":1,"right":116,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":4,"right":119,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":123,"right":127,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":7,"right":122,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":126,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":10,"right":125,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":125,"left":124,"right":13,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":153,"right":227,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":147,"right":152,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":147,"left":132,"right":146,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":132,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":135,"right":145,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":135,"left":19,"right":134,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":134,"left":20,"right":133,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":133,"left":21,"right":22,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"le